<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,261,775]" pageId="10" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,674,700]" pageId="10" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[332,631,675,700]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternoptychidae" genus="Sternoptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stomiiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudobscura">
<emphasis box="[332,631,675,700]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="44">Sternoptyx pseudobscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first reported in Brazilian waters by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima" box="[1155,1310,674,700]" pageId="10" pageNumber="48" refString="Lima, A. T. (2010) Sternoptyx pseudobscura Baird, 1971. In: Lavrado, H. P. &amp; Brasil, A. C. S. (eds.). Biodiversidade da regiao oceanica profunda da Bacia de Campos: megafauna e ictiofauna demersal. SAG Serv, Rio de Janeiro, pp. 328 - 329." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Lima (
<number box="[1238,1302,674,700]" pageId="10" pageNumber="44" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on material collected in Campos Basin, off Rio de Janeiro State. Specimens previously reported in the western South Atlantic were collected outside of the Brazilian Exclusive Economic Zone (
<bibRefCitation author="Badcock" box="[1111,1388,749,775]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" refString="Badcock, J. &amp; Baird, R. C. (1980) Remarks on systematics, development, and distribution of the genus Sternoptyx (Pisces, Stomiatoidei). Fishery Bulletin, 77 (4), 803 - 820." type="journal article" year="1980">
Badcock &amp; Baird 
<number box="[1325,1388,749,775]" pageId="10" pageNumber="44" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
